Two officers of the Department of State Services (DSS) have been reportedly killed following Sunday’s clash with the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) members in Enugu State.
The Public Relations Officer of the DSS, Peter Afunaya disclosed this in a statement on Sunday, revealing that a patrol team was attacked in the Emene area by IPOB members.
DSS condoled with the families of the murdered officers, and prayed for the repose of the departed souls.
The agency announced that all measures have been put in place to ensure that their killers and everyone involved in the act are apprehended and brought to justice.
“Consequently, a full-scale investigation will be carried out with regard to the incident.”
